Layout (per zip)
----------------

  duckdb.h            C API header
  duckdb.hpp          C++ API header
  libduckdb.so        Shared library (linked into emulator_main)
  libduckdb_static.a  Static archive (not linked today)

Why prebuilt and not from-source
--------------------------------

A from-source DuckDB build adds 4–7 minutes to a clean build (DuckDB
ships ~600k lines of C++) and pulls in its own vendored copies of RE2,
fast_float, fmt, fsst, and miniz. The upstream "libduckdb" release zips
ship a single .so / .a + duckdb.h + duckdb.hpp that we drop in verbatim,
so first-build time on CI is dominated by the network fetch (~40 MB)
instead of compilation.

Bumping the pin
---------------

1. Pick the new release tag from https://github.com/duckdb/duckdb/releases.
2. Download `libduckdb-linux-amd64.zip` from that release and run
   `sha256sum` on it (arm64 is captured here too for future reference,
   but only amd64 is wired into the Bazel build today).
3. Update the version and the amd64 SHA-256 hash in this file and in
   the `http_archive(name = "duckdb_linux_amd64", ...)` block in
   `MODULE.bazel`.
4. `task emulator:build-engine-bazel` and
   `ldd bin/emulator_main | grep libduckdb.so` to verify the binary
   still links cleanly.
